.TH TP-LINT 1 "2026-02-15" "Daniel Nylander" "tp-lint Manual"
.SH NAME
tp-lint - Lint PO files from the Translation Project
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tp-lint
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ LANGUAGE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBtp-lint\fR fetches and lints PO translation files from the Translation Project (translationproject.org). It downloads all translations for a language team, runs quality checks via l10n-lint, provides translation coverage statistics per language and package, and supports multiple output formats.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I LANGUAGE
Language code to lint (e.g., sv, de, fr).
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
List all available languages.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-stats " " \fI[LANG]\fR
Show translation statistics (default: global).
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-domain " " \fIPACKAGE\fR
Show statistics for a specific package/domain.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-top " " \fIN\fR
Number of top entries to show (default: 15).
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-report " " \fI[LANG]\fR
Generate a coverage report.
.TP
.BR \-\-report\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Report format: markdown, html (default: markdown).
.TP
.BR \-\-report\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Save report to file.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: text, json, github (default: text).
.TP
.B \-\-strict
Treat warnings as errors.
.TP
.BR \-k ", " \-\-keep
Keep downloaded PO files.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIDIR\fR
Output directory for downloaded PO files (implies \-\-keep).
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
tp-lint sv
tp-lint --list
tp-lint --stats sv
tp-lint --stats global --top 20
tp-lint -d coreutils sv
tp-lint --report sv --report-format html --report-output report.html
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/tp-lint/
Configuration files.
.TP
.I ~/.cache/tp-lint/
Cached data.
